# Document title vs buckets

When an MOI has a curated **document title** (e.g. "Resolution for new director appointment"):

- **Visible item name** for all parties: use `documentTitle` via `jobDisplayTitle()` — it replaces the generic **type of document / service** label in lists, carousels, workboards, and attention queues.
- **Category buckets stay unchanged**: group and filter with `resolveServiceCategory(job.service)` (or package service key). Never bucket or re-categorize by `documentTitle`.

Type of document / package service remains the structural identity; document title is display-only naming once saved.
